overview: 'The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application
  to verify its adherence to the provided specifications. The core intent was to
  identify and implement missing acceptance criteria. The approach involved
  systematically addressing several key areas: a 1-10 severity scale for
  tiredness with critical safety messaging was integrated into the questionnaire
  and reports; detection logic for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA)
  and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome was added, complete with tailored
  recommendations; a dedicated "Resources & Next Steps" section with relevant
  external links was incorporated into both the web and PDF reports; and the
  scoring for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) was enhanced with a weighted
  system to better reflect symptom severity. These implementations significantly
  improved the diagnostic capabilities and user guidance of the questionnaire,
  moving it closer to the comprehensive vision outlined in the Statement of
  Work.'
